  "body": "/kind feature \r\nThis issue is to ensure that the there is a node authorizer rule added to ensure that Kubelets are only allowed to access CSI VolumeAttachment objects related to the node.  For instance, during volume.SetupAt,  the CSI code creates a VolumeAttachment and saves it as an API object.  The authorizer would ensure that the new object can only come from a pod corresponding to volume referenced by a pod scheduled on that node.\r\n\r\n(See https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/56533#pullrequestreview-79728137)\r\n\r\nInfo resources for Authorizer\r\n- Authorizer proposal - https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/design-proposals/node/kubelet-authorizer.md#node-authorizer\r\n- Authorizer code https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/node/\r\n- Kubelet Authorizer - https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/design-proposals/node/kubelet-authorizer.md#node-authorizer",
